Function Signature: `function extractURLsFromCode(code: string): string[]`

For example, given the following JavaScript code snippet:
```javascript
<div>
    {mostUsedScriptures.map(s => {
        return (
            <Link to={s.to}>
                <OutlineScriptureChapter />
            </Link>
        );
    })}
</div>
```
The function `extractURLsFromCode` should return `['s.to']`.

Assume the following:
- The input code snippet will be well-formed and contain valid JavaScript syntax.
- The `Link` components will always have a `to` attribute representing the URL.

